    All Classes and Interfaces

    Classes
    Class
    Description
    App
    Class in which the individual application is started
    Constants
    Queries storage, here we have all the teams and players queries to get information, insert new data, update data or delete it
    CreatePlayerWindow
    Form to create a new player
    CreateTeamWindow
    Window with the form to add a new team, asking for each of its attributes except the list of players
    Database
    Class to access Database
    DeletePlayerWindow
    Selection to eliminate a player
    DeleteTeamWindow
    Window to select the equipment to delete
    EditPlayerWindow
    Form to edit a user collected by their ID
    EditTeamWindow
    Window with the form to edit the previously selected equipment, each input comes with the values ​​of the equipment
    ExcelGenerator
    Class that works as an excel generator
    ListTeamsWindow
    Window to list all teams and their respective information except their list of players
    Main
     
    PDFGenerator
    Class that works as a pdf generator
    Player
    Class to save a player information with the id, name, positions and team id
    PlayerDAO
    Class to access database data
    PlayerDetailsWindow
    Window to display the details of the player previously selected by his ID
    SelectPlayerDetailsWindow
    Window to select a player and then display his details
    SelectPlayerEditWindow
    Window to select the player that will later be edited
    SelectTeamDetailsWindow
    Preview window to select the equipment to display all its information, shows the list of all available equipment to select
    SelectTeamEditWindow
    Window to select the equipment we want to edit, shows a list of all the equipment available to select
    SplashScreen
    Class that stores the application's Splash Screen
    Team
    Class to save all the team information like the id, name, city and stadium
    TeamDAO
    Class to access all the database information
    TeamDetailsWindow
    Window with all the information about the teams including their list of players
    TeamPlayers
    Useful class to get the team information with the Team class, and including the player list
    TeamTableConverter
    Class that work like a helper to convert the objects in a multidimensional array to set in a table
